casebody.data:
WILLIAM J. SCHWENN, PLAINTIFF-APPELLANT, v. S. GOLDBERG & CO., INC., A CORPORATION OF NEW JERSEY, DEFENDANT-RESPONDENT. Superior Court of New Jersey Appellate Division Argued May 16, 1966 Decided June 6, 1966.

Before Judges Coneokd, Kilkenny and Leonabd.

Mr. Ralph W. Chandless argued the cause for appellant (Messrs. Chandless, Weller & Kramer, attorneys). Mr. Jacob Schneider argued the cause for respondent (Mr. E. Dennis Brod, on the brief). Per Curiam.

Judgment is affirmed substantially for the reasons expressed in the opinion of Judge Botter in the Law Division, 88 N. J. Super. 113 (1965).
